https://twitter.com/stevehofstetter/status/1522565429725736962?s=21&t=GMyVhTd5VVU9HK1jOGf0vQ</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/jlIvIA1</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[ridiculousbudget]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Lithops are South African plants that have evolved to look like stones</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/BkTpQP8</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/QrTmvm8.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Lithops is a genus of succulent plants in the ice plant family, Aizoaceae. Members of the genus are native to southern Africa. The name is derived from the Ancient Greek words λίθος (líthos), meaning "stone," and ὄψ (óps), meaning "face," referring to the stone-like appearance of the plants. They avoid being eaten by blending in with surrounding rocks and are often known as pebble plants or living stones. The formation of the name from the Ancient Greek "-ops" means that even a single plant is called a Lithops.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/BkTpQP8</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Satci]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>.nnnɒƨƨɒ⅃ ,υoγ ʞɔυꟻ</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/mURns0c</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/GpWBeyt.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/mURns0c</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Lassannn]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I’ll Take That</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/77NW3dl</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/a2nTCXX.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>#dog #drumstick #yoink #funny #illtakethat</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/77NW3dl</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[MartyIndependence]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I want in</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/7LNRfEf</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img a